Zamfara State Governor, Bello Matawalle, has appointed New Telegraph Correspondent in the state, Mallam Idris Salisu, Press Secretary in the Office of the Government of Zamfara State. Until his appointment, Salisu was engaged at various times with Hotline Magazine, Daily Independent newspapers, the defunct Union newspapers, General Manager (GM), National Newsline Magazine, a Kaduna-based magazine established by Bello Matawalle five years ago, and of recent, the state correspondent of the New Telegraph newspapers. In union matters, Idris had offered long time contribution as state Financial Secretary, vice-chairman and treasurer of the Nigerian Union of Journalists (NUJ) Zamfara State chapter. The appointment letter signed by the Secretary to the State Government, Alhaji Bala Bello Maru, said the engagement was with immediate effect.